HEADWORD: Lates
<hw>La"tes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ a
fish of the Nile.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of large
percoid fishes, of which one species (<spn>Lates Niloticus</spn>)
inhabits the Nile, and another (<spn>Lates calcarifer</spn>) is found in
the Ganges and other Indian rivers. They are valued as food
fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

